# Testing

## Purpose

Define when and how to test as the codebase grows.

## When It Applies

Adding tests, CI setup, and reviewing test coverage. See `docs/TESTING.md`.

## Requirements

- Unit tests for `@repo/utils` and pure business logic in services.
- Integration tests for API routes and repository adapters.
- No tests that hit production DB; use mocks or test containers.
- Test file colocation: `*.test.ts` next to source or in `__tests__/`.
- Run tests before marking sprint tasks complete (when test runner exists).

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ Pure function test
expect(slugify('Hello World')).toBe('hello-world');

// ✅ Service test with mocked repository
const repo = { findById: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(mockUser) };
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Testing implementation details of shadcn internals
// ❌ Snapshot-only tests with no assertion meaning
// ❌ Tests requiring real SUPABASE_URL in CI
```
